[3]
Date: Thu, 25 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: EpiNorth website, press release, 25 Aug 2005 [edited]
<http://www.epinorth.org>

[EpiNorth is a Cooperation Project for Communicable Disease Control in
Northern Europe, under the auspices of EU and the Nordic Council of
Ministers. It provides English translations of the latest official Russian
press releases on the avian influenza situation in Russia.]
On the sanitary-epidemiological situation in the Russian Federation,
updated 25 Aug 2005
---------------------------------------------------
The situation regarding illness in humans in connection with the avian
influenza A /H5N1/ bird epizootic, is stable as of 24 Aug 2005.
The epizootic has been detected in 45 districts in 7 constituent
territories of the Russian Federation (Novosibirsk, Omsk, Tyumen, Kurgan,
Chelyabinsk oblasts, Altay Kray and the Kalmykia Republic). The disease has
been found in wild and domestic birds in private farmsteads belonging to
citizens. Illness in humans who have been in contact with the infected
birds has not been detected.
In Novosibirsk oblast, 27 settlements in 8 regions are under observation.
No mass die-off has been registered during the last 24 hours. In 2
settlements, medical observation has ended.
In Omsk oblast, the epizootic was registered in 15 settlements, in 13 of
which deaths of domestic birds were recorded; in 2, only deaths of wild
birds. In the last 24 hrs, mass die-offs of birds have not been recorded;
medical observation was ceased in 2 villages.
In Tyumen oblast: mass die-offs of birds have not been registered. In 6
villages, all the domestic birds have been [culled] and in one settlement,
the quarantine has been lifted.
In Altay Kray 17 villages in 10 districts were affected by the epizootic.
In 5 settlements, medical observation has been discontinued and the
quarantine has been lifted. Mass die-offs in domestic birds has not been
recorded over the last 24 hours.
In Kurgan oblast, the quarantine has been lifted in one of the 21
settlements previously affected by the epizootic.
In Chelyabinsk oblast, mass die-offs in domestic birds have not been noted.
Medical observation and quarantine measures continue.
In the Republic of Kalmykia [where hunting is quite popular], cases of
illness in humans or mass die-offs of domestic birds have not been
registered. The quarantine has been lifted.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The data from Kalmykia, a province in SE European Russia on the Caspian
Sea, are ambiguous. In earlier reports it was stated that the presence of
HPAI there was not confirmed; however, according to the current statement
of the Russian minister of agriculture and the press release cited by
EpiNorth, Kalmykia was affected. This issue is expected to be clarified in
an official update by the Russian veterinary services. - Mod.AS].
